<TITLE> 5 workers hurt in fire at Sitakunda ship breakers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Sep 5 (bdnews24.com)  Five workers suffered burns in a fire at a ship breaking yard at Baro Aulia in Sitakunda on Saturday, two of whom are in critical condition, officials said. "The fire originated from a gas torch at around 10am, injuring five workers who were breaking a Korean ship at Kabir Steel Ship Yard," Mohammad Azam, sub-inspector of Sitakunda Police Station, told bdnews24.com. The injured workers were named as Md Ashek, 20, Kuddus, 32, Mohammad Hossain, 35, Md Jahangir, 28, and Khokon, 22. They were admitted to the Chittagong Medical College Hospital. The condition of Ashek and Kuddus is critical, said Ayyub Ali, head of the burns unit at CMCH. Eighty percent of Kuddus' body and 50 percent of Ashek's body are covered in burns, he said. b
